I’m attempting to set up PathPlanner for the first time with a variation of the BroncBotz3481 YAGSL example project. The example has PathPlanner in it already, but the 2024 version is slightly different and I’m having difficulty adapting it.

PathPlanner requires some methods to be used that aren’t already created, and I’m struggling to figure out how to write them. I’ve searched around and every version of PathPlanner being used that I’ve found is either using last year’s version or is too complicated for me to understand. The new/different methods are resetPose, driveRobotRelative and getRobotRelativeSpeed. I have a general understanding of their purpose, but that’s as far as I get.

Trying to learn swerve drive/YAGSL this year already has my head swimming, so adding on PathPlanner is a bit overwhelming at this point. Any guidance would be appreciated.

I really don’t understand how I had an issue - when I was installing the library, I was getting error messages about eg. resetOdometry being replaced with resetPose. So I commented out the original code and tried building it with what’s in the PathPlanner docs (Getting Started | PathPlanner Docs).

I just cleared out that code and uncommented the original example code - and it’s not throwing errors now. I have no idea what’s different, but I’m not going to fight it.

I’m going to chalk it up to mental exhaustion.

Thanks for the help!
